(Claparède, 1868)
</taxonomicName>
. A. Neotype (MNHN-A507), complete in lateral view. B. Same, anterior end, lateral view. C. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. D. Paraneotype, head, palps and branchiae detached (BS: branchial scars, DL: dorsal lip, LL: lateral lip). E. Non-type specimen (MNHN-A185), exposed anterior end, palps and branchiae detached (BS: branchial scars, Ca: caruncle, Pr: prostomium, PS: palp scar). F. Paraneotype, notochaetal regions, basal, median, distal and an enlargement of the tip. G. Same, neurochaetae from a median chaetiger, insert showing one tip. H. Same, neurochaetae from a posterior chaetiger, insert showing one tip. Scale bars: A: 3 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 1 mm, D–E: 0.5 mm, F: 50 µm, G: 200 µm, H: 25 µm.
